South Africa's Darren Adonis (L) fights for the ball with Australia's Joaquin De La Vega during the Men's HSBC World Rugby Sevens 2022 Final. AFP/Cristina Quicler JOHANNESBURG - The Blitzboks have claimed yet another World Rugby Sevens title. They ran out 33-7 winners over Australia in the Cup Final, which included five tries. Christoffel Grobbelaar scored two of those tries. This is the fourth consecutive win in this year's series after two wins in Dubai, one in Malaga and now in Seville. The series now moves to Singapore with the Blitzboks leading Argentina by 18 points.